correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and not schema-consistent. Major issues: (1) Incoherent process context: temperature set to 100 °C with H2O2, but filmThickness (6 nm) and GPC derive from 177 °C H2O runs; the paper does not report 6 nm at 100 °C with H2O2. (2) Growth per cycle is wrong by an order of magnitude and unit: reported ~0.2 nm/cycle (2 Å/cycle) at 177 °C, but extraction uses 0.2 Å/cycle. (3) Dosing/purge times grossly incorrect: article gives breakthrough ≈7–8 min (DEZ) and 6–7 min (H2O2) at 100 °C, but extraction records 480 ms and 420 ms; units and values are off by ~10^3 and not traceable. (4) Pressure (0.1 mmHg) is not reported in the article; only a general reduced pressure range is mentioned. (5) Flow rates (10 “SCM-PER-MIN”) are fabricated; the only stated flow is minimum fluidization 31 sccm; precursor/co-reactant flows are not given. (6) NucleationPeriod (10 cycles) not reported. (7) SupercycleDesign provided though this is a binary process; sequence strings are reagent names and not grounded. (8) plasmaPower is set to null, violating the schema (object expected or omit if TALD). (9) Material properties largely fabricated and untraceable: refractive index, absorption coefficient, electrical properties, uniformity, conformality aspect ratio, roughness (AFM), film density (XRR), and filmComposition values (50%, 1:1) are not reported; only crystallinity (polycrystalline by XRD) is supported. (10) DeviceProperties (mobility, Vth, SS, on/off, structure) are not present in the article. (11) Carrier/purging gas marked “not specified” (string is permissible, but not informative). To correct: align process to a single reported condition set (e.g., 177 °C with H2O or 100 °C with H2O2); fix GPC to ~0.2 nm/cycle where applicable; convert dosing/purge times to the reported minutes (or ms) correctly; remove or omit plasmaPower; omit or leave empty optional sections rather than invent values; only include material/device properties explicitly reported; avoid unreported pressure/flow values or clearly traceable ones (e.g., 31 sccm for fluidization if appropriate).

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely non-traceable to the article and misses multiple reported processes. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes described in the paper are not represented as separate process objects: (a) 177 °C DEZ–H2O (10 and 30 cycles; 2 nm and 6 nm films, ~0.2 nm/cycle), (b) 50 °C DEZ–H2O2 (30 cycles), and (c) 100 °C DEZ–H2O2 (30 cycles). Only one mixed/incorrect process is given. (2) Film thickness and GPC are misassigned/incorrect: 6 nm and ~0.2 nm/cycle are specifically for 177 °C with H2O, not for 100 °C with H2O2; GPC is 0.2 nm/cycle (=2 Å/cycle), but the extraction lists 0.2 Å/cycle. (3) Dosing and purge times are wrong by orders of magnitude and units: article gives breakthrough/dose times ~7–8 min for DEZ and ~6–7 min for H2O2 at 100 °C; extraction records 480 ms and 420 ms. (4) Flow rates: article reports a minimum fluidization flow of 31 sccm; extraction uses 10 sccm without support. (5) Pressure, carrier gas, purging gas values are either invented or “not specified” without traceability; specific pressure is not reported in the paper. (6) Many material and device properties are fabricated and not reported: refractive index, absorption coefficient, resistivity, carrier density, mobility, uniformity (%), conformality aspect ratio, roughness (AFM), film density (XRR), and all TFT device metrics. (7) Nucleation period (10 cycles) is not reported. (8) Schema misuse: plasmaPower is set to null (should be omitted if not PEALD), and supercycle details are assumed. To improve, add separate processes for each condition reported (177 °C/H2O with 10 and 30 cycles; 50 °C/H2O2/30 cycles; 100 °C/H2O2/30 cycles), correct GPC to 2 Å/cycle for the 177 °C/H2O case, use dosing times in minutes (converted to milliseconds per schema), include the 31 sccm fluidization flow, and remove or leave unspecified any properties not reported (optical, electrical, device, uniformity, conformality, roughness, density).
